      • subFDR

        protected <T extends FDRSelfAdd<T>> double subFDR(ArrayList<T> group,
                                                  ArrayList<T> results,
                                                  boolean setElementFDR,
                                                  SubGroupFdrInfo info,
                                                  boolean directional)
        Takes a sub-set of entries and does the actual FDR-estimation/cutoff.

        The assumption is that we have a symmetric cross-linker.
        Therefore:

        FP(TT)=TD+DD*(1-TDdb/DDdb)

        If TCount and DCount are of different size then the false positive estimation gets scaled accordingly.

        Type Parameters:
        T - What type of Information is the FDR to be applied
        Parameters:
        group - All entries for which the target FDR should be calculated
        fdr - the target FDR that is supposed to be returned
        safetyfactor - don't report anything if the next higher calculable exceeds the target-FDR by the given factor
        results - the passing results will be added to this ArrayList
        TCount - Size of the target database
        DCount - size of the decoy database
        info - all informations needed for this sub group
        isSymmetric - do we calculate an FDR for a symmetric or an asymmetric experiment
        setElementFDR -
        Returns:
